div.p: When a park record is changed, several things are put into motion. The record itself is either added/updated/or deleted from the NameReister Table in DynamoDB. A Dynamo Lambda Trigger stream is detected as a result of the table having such a configuration. The ProcessDynamoDBStream lambda is executed, and creates an appropriate record in the Audit table. In addition to this, it calls the OpenSearch managed service and inserts, updates, or deletes the record from the search service via main-index (you can have multiple indexes in a single OS Cluster). The Process stream lambda and OpenSearch services are configured to be within the App-A designated VPC. This ensures only items we place into the VPC are able to query and index the data that is within the OS cluster.

div.p: When a client uses the search lambda, it executes in the VPC environment. It contacts the OpenSearch service and will hit the main-index looking for a full-text search for the given query. Depending on who is calling the endpoint, notes field (or others) can be redacted before returning the payload. Modifications on field weight, fuzziness, etc can be configured to fine tune the response results.
